title: US Dollar LIBOR Three Month Rate
description: US Dollar LIBOR Three Month Rate was at 4.56 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in the United States averaged 3.51 percent from 1986 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 10.63 percent in March of 1989 and a record low of 0.11 percent in September of 2021. The three month US Dollar LIBOR interest rate is the average interest rate at which a LIBOR contributor bank can obtain unsecured funding in the London interbank market for a three month period in US dollars. This page provides - United States Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
